article.headline: Toledo 64, Arkansas State 63
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Sam Villegas sank a 3-pointer with nine seconds left to complete a second-half rally and beat Arkansas State 64-63 Wednesday night. Toledo (4-0) trailed by 16 at the half, but hit five 3-pointers to make it 63-61 with 16 seconds left. Justin Ingram picked off a pass by the Indians' Tevoris Thompson and hit Villegas for the winning shot. Following Villegas' score, Arkansas State (3-1) passed to Dewarick Spencer, who drove to the right side baseline. Spencer wasn't able to get the shot off as time ran out. Villegas led the Rockets with 17 points and four rebounds. Ingram followed with 14 points and three assists. No other Rockets made double-digits. The Indians were only 12-of-25 on free throws, despite leading the Sun Belt Conference in free throw percentage as a team the last two seasons. The Indians jumped out to a 9-point lead early in the first half, with Spencer scoring 14 of his 19 points for the night. J.J. Montgomery led with 22 points and 13 rebounds. Tevoris Thompson had 12.
